<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-62-0069 </DOCNO><TEXT>The main results reported by an &quot;Ad Hoc&quot; working group established bythe CSIA-ATI are presented and discussed, with particular reference tothe Italian situation in comparison with other EEC countries. In particular,air pollution control systems of exhaust gases from petrol operated carsare reviewed with reference to the actual prospects of practical applicationand the influence on the energy economy. The effectiveness of additivesand alternative fuels are also examined.</TEXT></DOC>